		"notes": [
			{
				"category": "summary",
				"text": "An update for thunderbird is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8.1 Update Services for SAP Solutions.\n\nRed Hat Product Security has rated this update as having a security impact of Critical. A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE link(s) in the References section.",
				"title": "Topic"
			},
			{
				"category": "general",
				"text": "Mozilla Thunderbird is a standalone mail and newsgroup client.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* nss: Memory corruption in decodeECorDsaSignature with DSA signatures (and RSA-PSS) (CVE-2021-43527)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
				"title": "Details"
			},
